As demonstrated for BEO, NanoBEO has proven analgesic efficacy both in the inflammatory pain models of the capsaicin (59.26% improvement over control, ** 
 p < 0.01; 
 Figure 2) and the formalin test (59.78% improvement over control, ** 
 p < 0.01; 
 Figure 3) and in the neuropathic pain model of the PSNL (58.76% improvement over control, ** 
 p < 0.01; 
 Figure 4). In comparison with the empty NDS (control), NanoBEO was also effective in preventing 4-methyl-histamine-induced scratching behavior (
 Figure 5a,b). The effect of NanoBEO on itching is reported in a short movie within the 
 Supplementary Materials.
